\pard\fi199\sl-238\slmult0\qj\tx198 The stars and Galaxies died and snuffed out, and space grew black after ten trillion years of \fs20 running \fs22 down.\par
One by one Man fused with AC, each physical body losing its mental identity in a manner that was somehow not a loss but a gain.\par
\f1 Man\rquote s last mind paused before fusion, looking over a space that included nothing but the dregs of one last dark star and nothing besides but incredibly thin matter, agitated randomly by the tag ends of heat wearing out, asymptotically, to the absolute zero.\f0\par
\f1 Man said, \ldblquote AC, is this the end? Can this chaos not be reversed into the Universe once more? Can that not be done?\rdblquote\f0\par
\pard\fi204\sl-238\slmult0\qj\tx204 AC said, \b\f1\fs16\ldblquote THERE IS AS YET INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR A MEANINGFUL ANSWER.\rdblquote\f0\par
\pard\sl-238\slmult0\qj\tx204\par
\pard\fi199\sl-238\slmult0\qj\tx198\b0\f1\fs22 Man\rquote s last mind fused and only AC existed-and that in hyper\f0\-space.\par
\pard\sl-238\slmult0\qj\tx198\par
\pard\fi199\sl-238\slmult0\qj\tx198 Matter and energy had ended and with it space and time. Even AC existed only for the sake of the one last question that it had never answered from the time a half-drunken computer ten trillion years before had asked the question of a computer that was to AC far less than was a man to Man.\par
All other questions had been answered, and until this last ques\-tion was answered also, AC might not release his consciousness.\par
All collected data had come to a final end. Nothing was left to be collected.\par
But all collected data had yet to be completely correlated and put together in all possible relationships.\par
\pard\fi397\sl-498\slmult0\qj\tx396 A timeless interval was spent in doing that.\par
\f1 And it came to pass that AC learned how to reverse the direction of entropy.\par
But there was now no man to whom AC might give the answer of the last question. No matter.\par
The answer ---- by demonstration---- would take care of that, too. For another timeless \par
interval, AC thought how best to do this. Carefully, AC organized the program. \par
The consciousness of AC encompassed all of what had once been a Universe and brooded\par
over what was now Chaos. Step by step, it must be done.\par
And AC said, "\b LET THERE BE LIGHT!"\par
